The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Wednesday, March 17, 2004 				 Mother pushes girl out of train
																								Ghaziabad, March 16 (PTI): An 18-year-old unmarried pregnant girl was thrown out of a running train near Kaili railway station last night by her mother and maternal grandparents, police said.																								Inspector-general of police for Meerut zone R.K. Tiwari said the incident occurred when the girl, Kishori, was being taken for an abortion by her mother and grandparents.																								Tiwari said the three have been arrested. He added that a case has been registered against them and two unidentified persons who had helped them in throwing the girl. 																								The duo, however, managed to escape.																								He said travellers on the Khurja-Meerut Passenger opposed Kishoris mother and brought the train to a halt by pulling the chain.																								Kishori was taken to the P.L. Sharma hospital at Meerut where she delivered a stillborn girl.																								In January this year, Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayees grandnephew was pushed off speeding Chhattisgarh Express for protesting against eve- teasing.
